  "local_port": 50158,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I get call history for my Airtel prepaid number?",
  "response": "To retrieve your call history for your Airtel prepaid number, you have several options:\n\n### 1. **Through the Airtel Thanks App**  \n   - Download the **Airtel Thanks App** from the Google Play Store or Apple App Store.  \n   - Log in with your Airtel prepaid number.  \n   - Navigate to the **Usage** or **Account** section.  \n   - You should find a **Call History** or **Statement** option where you can view your recent call details.  \n\n### 2. **Via SMS**  \n   - Send an SMS with the text **LAST** to **121** or **56777**.  \n   - You will receive an SMS with a link to your call history details.  \n\n### 3. **Using the USSD Code**  \n   - Dial ***121#** on your Airtel number.  \n   - Select the **My Account** or **View Usage** option.  \n   - Look for the **Call History** or **Detailed Statement** option.  \n\n### 4. **Online on the Airtel Website**  \n   - Visit the official Airtel website: [www.airtel.in](https://www.airtel.in).  \n   - Log in to your Airtel account using your prepaid number.  \n   - Go to the **Usage** or **Account** section to view your call history.  \n\n### 5. **Customer Care**  \n   - Call Airtel customer care at **121** or **198** from your Airtel number.  \n   - Follow the IVR instructions to request your call history.  \n   - You may need to verify your identity.  \n\n### Note:  \n- Call history details are typically available for the **last 30 days**.  \n- Some methods may require you to authenticate your identity for security purposes.  \n\nChoose the method that works best for you!",
